Class EncryptedPutObjectRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.cloud.objectstorage.AmazonWebServiceRequest
      • com.ibm.cloud.objectstorage.services.s3.model.AbstractPutObjectRequest
        • com.ibm.cloud.objectstorage.services.s3.model.PutObjectRequest
          • com.ibm.cloud.objectstorage.services.s3.model.EncryptedPutObjectRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HandlerContextAware, ReadLimitInfo, MaterialsDescriptionProvider, S3DataSource, SSEAwsKeyManagementParamsProvider, SSECustomerKeyProvider, Serializable, Cloneable

    public class EncryptedPutObjectRequest
extends PutObjectRequest
implements MaterialsDescriptionProvider, Serializable

    This class is an extension of PutObjectRequest to allow additional encryption material description to be specified on a per-request basis.In particular, EncryptedPutObjectRequest is only recognized by AmazonS3EncryptionClient.

    If EncryptedPutObjectRequest is used against the non-encrypting AmazonS3Client, the additional attributes will be ignored.
